DataElement.preferredDefinition: The yes/no response to a question that asks whether an application has been submitted.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Biomarker Imaging Quality of Life Studies Funding Program Application Submission
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Information pertaining to the application for a funding mechanism and prioritization process for essential correlative studies and quality of life studies that are incorporated into the fundamental design of a clinical trial being submitted.

ObjectClass.preferredName: Biomarker Imaging Quality of Life Studies Funding Program
ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A funding mechanism and prioritization process for essential correlative studies and quality of life studies that are incorporated into the fundamental design of a clinical trial.  The objective of this initiative is to ensure that the most important biomarker, imaging, and quality of life studies can be initiated in a timely manner in association with late phase clinical trials.
